    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <completion-notes>
      Path A.5 binding implemented per task 030 decision doc (final § "Confirmation — IPlaybookService survey result"). HandleNarrate now a thin dispatch wrapper: (1) `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync(ConsumerTypes.DailyBriefingNarrate, "default", null, null, ct)` resolves playbook GUID `7b5a6ed3-0271-f111-ab0e-000d3a13a4cd`; (2) request serialized as `briefingPayload` parameter + 4 scalar convenience keys; (3) `IInvokePlaybookAi.InvokePlaybookAsync(...)` invokes the playbook; (4) `ProjectPlaybookResultToNarrateResponse` maps `StructuredData` → `DailyBriefingNarrateResponse` (TL;DR + ChannelNarratives + GeneratedAtUtc — backward-compat shape preserved per AC-12b).

      Inline LLM-prompt helpers removed: `BuildNarrateTldrPrompt`, `BuildChannelNarrationPrompt`, `ParseTldrResponse`, `ParseChannelBullets`, `BuildAllowedRegardingIdSet`, `ValidateBulletPrimaryEntityIds`, `GetTldrAsync`, `GetChannelNarrationAsync`, `TldrJsonPayload` (~340 LOC dead code purged). Reflection-based regression test added (`DailyBriefingEndpoints_Source_Has_No_Inline_LLM_Prompt_Helpers`) enforces AC-12a.

      Empty-payload tolerance + 503 fail-fast (re-targeted to routing-null path) preserved. `IBriefingAi?` parameter removed from HandleNarrate (still used by sibling `Summarize` endpoint — out of scope for FR-12).

      `sprk_playbookconsumer` row deployed to spaarkedev1: id `b4503359-1771-f111-ab0e-7ced8ddc4a05` (sprk_consumertype="daily-briefing-narrate", sprk_consumercode="default", sprk_environment="*", sprk_priority=500, sprk_enabled=true, sprk_playbook=`7b5a6ed3-0271-f111-ab0e-000d3a13a4cd`, statecode=0).

      `ConsumerTypes.DailyBriefingNarrate = "daily-briefing-narrate"` constant added (+ `ConsumerTypes.All` list updated for chat-routing-redesign-r1 task 028e startup health-log diffing).

      Build: ✅ clean (17 pre-existing warnings, 0 errors). Tests: ✅ 10/10 DailyBriefingEndpoints + 7873/7873 full suite (134 skipped — matches baseline). Publish: 46.30 MB (-0.01 MB vs PR 3 baseline 46.31 MB). CVE: ✅ no new HIGH (1 pre-existing Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2 unchanged).

      **Component Justification (CLAUDE.md §11)** — Existing: hardcoded HandleNarrate body. Extension: Yes — REPLACES existing implementation via DI of the already-registered facades (`IConsumerRoutingService` + `IInvokePlaybookAi`). Cost-of-doing-nothing: hallucination persists; prompts cannot iterate without recompile (concrete R3 UAT defect). No new component introduced — endpoint is now the 7th caller of the existing routing-facade pattern (6 prior callers: `MatterPreFillService`, `ProjectPreFillService`, `WorkspaceAiService`, `WorkspaceFileEndpoints`, `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`, `AppOnlyAnalysisService`).

      Evidence: `notes/smoke/031-handle-narrate-rewrite.md`, `notes/debug/031-publish-size.md`, `notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md`.
    </completion-notes>
  <prompt>Edit `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/DailyBriefingEndpoints.cs` HandleNarrate (~line 189). Replace inline LLM-prompt construction with a thin wrapper that invokes the playbook engine per task 030's decision path. Dispatch playbook code `BRIEF-NARRATE`. Pass through the existing `DailyBriefingNarrateRequest` payload. Response shape MUST be backward compat — existing widget parser unchanged. NO inline prompt strings remain.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. BFF API + AI dispatch refactoring; replace inline LLM call with playbook engine invocation while preserving response contract.</role>
  <goal>HandleNarrate no longer constructs LLM prompts inline. It dispatches via the playbook path selected in task 030, mapping to playbook code `BRIEF-NARRATE`. Response JSON shape (top-level fields: `tldr`, `channelNarratives`, `generatedUtc`) is preserved exactly. `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` succeeds.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>R3 UAT defect: HandleNarrate hardcodes the LLM prompt body inside the endpoint, blocking iteration without recompile and contributing to hallucination. R4 FR-12 requires /narrate to be a thin dispatch wrapper to the existing playbook engine. Task 030 finalized the dispatch path (A = consumer registration, B = direct RunPlaybookAsync with degenerate playbook). This task implements that decision.</background>
